## Overview
This document explains how our unique ID generation system works. The system generates unique identifiers using specific letters and numbers, growing in length as needed to maintain uniqueness.

## Allowed Characters

### Letters (9 total):
P, L, Q, G, R, J, C, U, V

### Numbers (4 total):
0, 2, 8, 9

## ID Generation Rules

1. Basic Structure:
   - Minimum length: 3 characters
   - Must contain at least one letter
   - Can use any combination of allowed letters and numbers
   - No spaces or special characters

